{
  "doc_id": "4441",
  "text": "In the context of DNN model compression, the line of works [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] adopts a multi-step procedure in which the weights of a pretrained DNN are first pruned and the remaining parameters are quantized using a k-means like algorithm, the DNN is then retrained, and finally the quantized DNN model is encoded using entropy coding. A notable different approach is taken by [CITATION_4] , where the DNN compression task is tackled using the minimum description length principle, which has a solid information-theoretic foundation.",
